It will not bother me any more.
Quit now and you will not get a dime.
But how will you pay for tomorrow's groceries?
He should be safe down there.
Let us take this to Ayaka-san tomorrow.
I will pick you up in the morning.

I normally keep these powers suppressed.
Even you would get hurt by touching my blood now.

Kuriyama-san, are not you going to join a club?
I do not have time for one.
Are you interested in the Literary Club?
I would love to have a bespectacled beauty there.
You see, I am a member of the club.
There are only two of us, though.
Oh, the other member is an Exterminator as well,
so she could help you out with work as well.
I do not care to interact with others.
A beauty in glasses under the moon...
I am the one who finds this unpleasant!
She was up late last night, so she is still...
There was a demon I was hoping she could take a look at.
H-How can you speak with a demon as if she is a friend?!
Do not tell me you never noticed!
But she is not our enemy.
As you can see, she is no different from a normal person.
Demons come in all shapes and sizes!
We are even certified by the Exterminator's Society.
Under the provisions stated in Legislative Article 21, Section 1, this testifies that you are authorized to dispose of and appraise demons.
It is not like humans go around appraising other humans!
You should not lump all the demons together like that!
There are all sorts of us, ranging from insectoids to humanoids.
We are jumbled together sort of the same way mammals are.
For instance, you may both be mammals,
but humans appraise cows and pigs, right?
Well, when you put it that way...
How come you still seem unconvinced?
Oh, you have not met before?
Where the hell did that come from?!
And why are you playing along?!
Mitsuki, you know who this is, right?
So she is real after all.
What is that supposed to mean?
To be blunt, I thought you subconsciously created an imaginary girl
who looks cute in glasses and always ends her sentences with a meow,
since you are so pathetic and can only sustain yourself through escapism.
I am amazed at how you can insult me and be so casual about it.
If you are making her as quirky as possible, she should always shout, Yeah, glasses!
Actually, that does not sound half bad.
We really should be on our way.
Ai-chan, have you noticed anything unusual with the demons lately?
Well, I ran into one that was rather aggressive.
Do not know, do not care.
You stuck your nose where it did not belong, did not you?
Do not make it sound like it is my fault!
I am inviting you to come visit the Literary Club.
You have not joined any other clubs,
and there are not that many Exterminators at our school.
Plus you just got here, so
I believe I already turned that offer down.
Are you that against joining the Literary Club?
Did you give it a try?
I guess there is no other choice.
I will have to ask him first.
You forgot to put a Cage around the school the other day, did not you?
Thanks to you, I had to call the Cleaners!
I do not recall promising to keep a Cage around the school constantly.
It is not my job to specifically protect this campus.
There is something I would like to ask you.
You would have no reason to see me otherwise, Akkey.
Want me to tell you why I do not care to see your face?
Because demons and Exterminators mix as well as water and oil?
It is because that weird nickname you gave me makes it sound like I am some washed-up idol!
Always so energetic when it comes to that name.
I regret coming to you 30 seconds after you opened your mouth!
So, what did you want to ask?
I ran into a rather aggressive demon yesterday.
Any idea what could have agitated it?
Are you getting involved in things you should not again?
I will not raise a hand against you, Akkey.
In exchange, you are not supposed to offer anyone support.
What are your hands doing there?
Well, my fingers were getting cold.
Akkey, your waist is really something.
You should not freak out over a fellow man wrapping his hands around your waist.
All I am trying to say is that that your waist is pure and warm.
That does not make me the least bit happy!
Let us just get back to the topic at hand!
You mean why girls give you the cold shoulder?
I would like to know why, but not even close!
I am here about the demon!
Why do you want to know about that?
No, I am here on my own accord.
I am even less obligated to talk.
In other words, you do know what triggered it.
I believe I am giving you quite the deal.
After all my hard work, she is only giving me 20,000 yen!
We both know that demon was not all that aggressive, now was it?
It is strange for it to be like that.
I would like to run home and get changed before I head over.
What type of heroine attends a group blind date in wool panties?
She is as lively as ever.
So has a girl named Kuriyama-san dropped by?
Oh, you mean the case Ai texted me about?
By the way, have you set up a new barrier to ward people off?
Yeah, the old one was starting to wear off.
But the average Exterminator should be able to see through the new one.
It is hard to say whether or not she counts as average.
If I remember correctly, the Nase Manor is somewhere near the top of this hill.
I heard it is really huge!
I just cannot seem to find it.
I am sure it is around here somewhere.
Why are you with Senpai... Kanbara-senpai?
you could say I am watching him.
It looks like her thoughts are embedded into it.
Well, this postcard did come from my mother.
Akkun, have you been staying awesome?
Could you pretend that you never saw any of that?
Kanbara-kun, was that your mother just now?
She is always been in her own world!
On Parents' Day in elementary school, she always sat with the students and raised her hand.
She has such an avant-garde mindset!
Akihito, a strong sense of individuality and uniqueness is a great thing to have.
How long have you been there?
Since you said, I keep glasses worn by high school girls in vinyl bags,
and I get high huffing the air out of the bags.
The girl in glasses is Kuriyama-san, yes?
I am a demon, but please do not attack me.
You need to appraise Kuriyama-san's demon, so my letter can wait.
I would just love to hear the rest!
Even I can get embarrassed, you know!
Akane, it is true that cat-type demons are not too bright,
but you should not be embarrassed of your own mother!
My mother is not a demon.
We have been over this before!
Then how do you explain those ears?
It is all about the details for her.
The apple does not fall far from the tree, huh?
I just cannot talk you guys out of it!
Let us just get this over with!
You got to know when to hold and when to fold, Kanbara-kun.
I have something impurrtant to tell you,
so please be all ears to the end.
I think even the avant-garde community would award her for dancing like that.
Could you please stop talking about my mother?
Oh, but first off, are you eating right?
If you do not cook for yourself from time to time,
you will not get the nutrients you need.
A powerful demon is headed your way, my kitten!
Have mew ever heard of the Hollow Shadow?
The Hollow Shadow does not possess a physical body.
So no meowtter what, do not try to fight it!
Akkun, you are a good kitten, so I am sure you understand,
but make sure to steer clear of it!
Pinky promise that you will stay away from it, Akkun!
Is not it wonderful to have a busty mother with a few screws loose?
Anyway, what is this Hollow Shadow?
Just as she said, it is a powerful demon that lacks a physical body.
Rumor has it that the last time it appeared,
five Class A Exterminators did not last even five minutes.
What are we going to do if that comes here?
We will just have to wait for it to pass us by.
Could this be related to why the demons were so aggressive yesterday?
Low-level demons are easily influenced by the aura surrounding other demons.
So that is what it is.
Well, now that the show's over,
why do not we take a look at Kuriyama-san's demon?
All of that was just a show to you?!
Do not make my mother the source of your entertainment!
Where is the demon you caught?
If you would be so kind...
I worked so hard to take it down, and all I get is 1,000 yen?!
Well, that is just how it goes.
Well, you can just ignore Akihito.
If you run into trouble, come to me for advice.
